item.name: api/v1/models
Model Traits

request.description:
By default, this endpoint returns `text` models.

Docs can be found here: [https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits](https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits)

By default, this endpoint returns `text` models. By passing `image` as the type, the complete model list will be returned.

Docs can be found here: [https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits](https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits)

item.description:
Model traits provide an alias to models. You can use a trait as a model ID knowing it will always be mapped to a model at Venice, avoiding issues with models changing over time.

Docs can be found here: [https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits](https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/traits)

item.name: Model Compatibility Mapping

request.description:
Model Compatibility mappings allow users to input common model names from current AI platforms and have them mapped to the current equvilient version at Venice.

Docs can be found here: [https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/compatibility_mapping](https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/compatibility_mapping)

item.description:
Venice maintains a compatibility mapping of certain LLM model names to ensure compatibility with as many tools as possible.

This endpoint returns our current mappings.

item.name: Inpainting

body.raw:
{
  "return_binary": true,
  "model": "flux-dev",
  "prompt": "mask",
  "width": 1024,
  "height": 1024,
  "steps": 30,
  "safe_mode": false,
  "hide_watermark": true,
  "cfg_scale": 7.0,
  "inpaint": {
    "strength": 50,
    "mask": {
        "image_prompt": "Put harry botter rimmed glasses on the face",
        "object_target": "the face", 
        "inferred_object": "harry potter rimmed glasses"
    },
    "source_image_base64": ""
  }
}

request.description: Returns the current utilization rate in decimal format of the network.

Returns the current staking yield and staking metrics.

``` json
{
    "totalStaked": "9046425.274175347238396072",        // The total number of staked VVV
    "totalEmission": "38313.54642313546422313",         // Total VVV emissions over the last 24 hours
    "stakerDistribution": "30437.162735797382033993",   // Total VVV emissions emitted to stakers
    "stakingYield": "1.22806125755333435282"            // Staking yield
}

 ```

**Beta Note:**

This is a beta endpoint. It's format and query parameters are likely to change before it's finalized.
